{{TennisEventInfo|1987|Brasil Open| | date=7–13 December | edition=5th | draw=32S / 16D | prize_money=$50,000 | surface=[[Clay court|Clay]] | category=1 | location=[[Guarujá]], Brazil | champs={{flagicon|BRA|1968}} [[Neige Dias]] | champd={{flagicon|USA}} [[Katrina Adams]] / {{flagicon|USA}} [[Cheryl Jones]] }}
The '''1987 Brasil Open''' was a women's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] in [[Guarujá]] in Brazil and was part of the Category 1 tier of the [[1988 WTA Tour]]. The tournament ran from 7 December through 13 December 1987. [[Neige Dias]] won the singles title.<ref name=wot1989>{{cite book|title=The [[International Tennis Federation]] : World of Tennis 1989|year=1989|publisher=Willow Books|location=London|isbn=9780002183116|editor=[[John Barrett (tennis)|John Barrett]]|page=210}}</ref>
==Finals== ===Singles=== {{main|1987 Brasil Open – Singles}} {{flagicon|BRA|1968}} [[Neige Dias]] defeated {{flagicon|BRA|1968}} [[Patricia Medrado]] 6–0, 6–7<sup>(2–7)</sup>, 6–4 * It was Dias' only title of the year and the 2nd of her career.
===Doubles=== {{main|1987 Brasil Open – Doubles}} {{flagicon|USA}} [[Katrina Adams]] / {{flagicon|USA}} [[Cheryl Jones]] defeated {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Jill Hetherington]] / {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Mercedes Paz]] 6–4, 4–6, 6–4 * It was Adams' only title of the year and the 1st of her career. It was Jones' only title of the year and the 1st of her career.
