{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Khalifa bin Zayed Stadium | image = Sheikh Khalifa International Stadium.jpg | caption = | location = [[Al Ain]], [[UAE]] | broke_ground = | opened = 1996 | renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Al-Ain FC]] | operator = | surface = Grass | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | dimensions = | tenants = [[UAE national football team]] | seating_capacity = 16,000<ref name = a>{{cite web|last=|first=|url=https://int.soccerway.com/venues/united-arab-emirates/sheikh-khalifa-international-stadium/ |title=Sheikh Khalifa International Stadium|publisher=Soccerway|date=30 December 2010|accessdate=30 December 2010}}</ref> | title = Capacity | publisher = Worldstadia}}
'''Khalifa bin Zayed Stadium''' ({{lang-ar|استاد خليفة بن زايد}}) is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Al Ain]], [[United Arab Emirates]].<ref>[http://www.worldstadiums.com/stadium_pictures/middle_east/uae/al_ayn_stadium.shtml Sheikh Khalifa International Stadium], [http://www.worldstadiums.com/ World Stadiums].</ref>
One of the most famous events to be staged on this stadium was the group E matches of the [[2003 FIFA World Youth Championship]] and the stadium also hosted some matches from the [[1996 AFC Asian Cup]].{{citation needed|date=October 2010}}
The stadium is used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/venues/united-arab-emirates/sheikh-khalifa-international-stadium/ Sheikh Khalifa International Stadium Al Ain], [https://int.soccerway.com/ Soccerway].</ref> and is one of the home grounds of [[Al-Ain FC]]. The stadium was built to hold 12,000 people and as of the 2006/2007 season all the Al Ain team matches are played in this stadium.
The stadium's capacity was increased by another 4,000 so the new seating capacity is 16,000.{{citation needed|date=October 2010}} The stadium currently is undergoing a significant upgrade and renovation, to prepare for the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].
==2019 AFC Asian Cup== Sheikh Khalifa International Stadium will host six games of the 2019 AFC Asian Cup, including a Round of 16 match. {{anchor|AC2019}} {{clear}} {|class="wikitable" style="text-align:left; width:100%;" |- !Date !Time !Team No. 1 !Res. !Team No. 2 !Round !Attendance |- |7 January 2019||15:00|| {{fb|CHN}} ||style="text-align:center;"| Match 5 || {{fb|KGZ}} ||[[2019 AFC Asian Cup Group C|Group C]]||style="text-align:center;"| |- |10 January 2019||17:30|| {{fb|JOR}} ||style="text-align:center;"| Match 14 || {{fb|SYR}} ||[[2019 AFC Asian Cup Group B|Group B]]||style="text-align:center;"| |- |13 January 2019||15:00|| {{fb|PRK}} ||style="text-align:center;"| Match 22 || {{fb|QAT}} ||[[2019 AFC Asian Cup Group E|Group E]]||style="text-align:center;"| |--- |15 January 2019||17:30|| {{fb|AUS}} ||style="text-align:center;"| Match 27 || {{fb|SYR}} ||[[2019 AFC Asian Cup Group B|Group B]]||style="text-align:center;"| |- |17 January 2019||17:30|| {{fb|JPN}} ||style="text-align:center;"| Match 34 || {{fb|UZB}} ||[[2019 AFC Asian Cup Group F|Group F]]||style="text-align:center;"| |- |21 January 2019||18:00|| Runner-up Group B ||style="text-align:center;"| Match 41 || Runner-up Group F ||[[2019 AFC Asian Cup knockout stage|Round of 16]]||style="text-align:center;"| |}
