{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Use Australian English|date=January 2018}} '''Scanlens''' is a brand of [[trading card]]s first produced in the 1930s and given away with packets of [[candy|sweets]] and [[chewing gum]].<ref name="Thieves">{{cite news | title = Thieves make off with collector's cards | url = http://www.smh.com.au/news/National/Thieves-make-off-with-collectors-cards/2007/10/17/1192300831727.html | accessdate = 2009-04-14 | date = 2007-10-17 | quote = Scanlens first produced trading cards in the 1930s, '40s and '50s, which were given away with packets of chewing gum. | work=The Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref> The first sports-themed cards series were produced in limited quantities in 1963 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-interact.com.au/cardtrader/#changes|title=Football Changes Are on the Cards}}</ref> featuring 18 players from the [[Australian Football League|Victorian Football League]] which have since become highly sought after, with some cards commanding a price of up to $2000 each. Scanlens went on to produce further modern card sets (sport and non sport) between 1963 and 1989, many of which have since become collectors' items.<ref>{{cite news | title = Caulfield Glen Eira / Port Phillip Leader | url = http://www.newstext.com.au/docs/CKV/2006/get.jsp?docid=CKV-20060424-1-022-4096175V3@VIC-LEADER-2006-2005 | accessdate = 2009-04-14 | date = 2006-04-24 | quote = Scanlens cards are still very keenly sought after by collectors as not many exist in great}}</ref>
